    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1905-10-31T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1905-10-31T00:00:00-05:00" n="428"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d428">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">British Ambassador</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1905-10-31">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 31, 1905</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 343.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Excellency</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the
                    receipt of, and cordially to thank you for, your note No. 213, of the 27th
                    instant, regarding the Newfoundland fishery question.</p>
                <p>It will be equally agreeable to me that you should take the course you propose
                    with regard to my note of the 25th instant, in communicating to the Newfoundland
                    government, for the information of their people on the treaty coast, the
                    substance of my reply.</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Elihu Root.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
